HEADWORD: Trimurti
<hw>Tri*mur"ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>trim⟦umac⟧rti</ets>; <ets>tri</ets> three + <ets>m⟦umac⟧rti</ets>
body.]</ety> <fld>(Hindu Myth.)</fld> <def>The triad, or trinity, of
Hindu gods, consisting of Brahma, the Creator, Vishnu, the Preserver,
and Siva, the Destroyer.</def> <altsp>[Spelled also
<asp>Trimurtti</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
